events.title: Phone Bank for Sue Shink!
events.description:
Sue Shink is running for the new 14th Michigan State Senate District seat. If she wins, Democrats will take the Michigan State Senate for the first time in 40 years! If you're not able to knock doors, you can phone bank with us! 

We will send out a zoom link and phone bank link before your shift! If you need paper sheets, you can stop by Sue's home, 660 W Joy Rd in Ann Arbor, and we'll train you and give you some calls to make! 

Thanks for your help!

events.title: Canvass for Sue Shink!
events.description:
Sue Shink is running for the new 14th Michigan State Senate District seat. If she wins, Democrats will take the Michigan State Senate for the first time in 40 years! That is why it is so important to signup to knock on doors for Sue! 

We can accomodate you to knock doors in any area of the district or what is the biggest priority, as well as at anytime (the shift times and location are just suggested, sign up for the shift time that is closest to the one that works for you and when we contact you, just let us know what adjustment needs to be made timing or location wise).

 For first timers, we will train you to be an all-star door knocker, give you Sue Shink literature and yard signs, and your list number for Minivan. For seasoned vets, we will get you the literature (if you need it) and list number and you're off to the races! 

Let's get out on the doors, get Sue elected, win the Michigan State Senate, and enable a truly progressive agenda to be passed in Lansing next year!

events.title: Ann Arbor RFFA Canvass
events.description:
Join us for our next big action as we start door knocking in different locations all around the state! We'll be heading out to the doors to get voters engaged about the upcoming election and making sure this ballot initiative has enough votes to pass in November.
 
The United States Supreme Court issued an opinion in Jackson Womenâ€™s Health Organization v. Dobbs and overturned Roe v. Wade.

Important medical decisions should be guided by a patient's health and wellbeing, not by a politician's beliefs. But for too long, politicians across the country have been fighting to restrict reproductive health care, and now they are gaining ground.

If the U.S. Supreme Court overturns Roe v. Wade, an abortion ban from 1931 could go back into effect in Michigan, cutting off access to abortion for more than 2 million Michiganders and threatening doctors with prison.

Reproductive Freedom for All is a campaign to amend the Michigan Constitution. Our amendment would guarantee the right to reproductive freedom for all, and make sure Lansing politicians cannot interfere in our personal decisions.

Specifically, our proposal will affirm that every person has the fundamental right to reproductive freedom, which involves the right to make and carry out decisions without political interference about all matters relating to pregnancy, including birth control, abortion, infertility, miscarriage care, prenatal care, and childbirth.

Sign up today to help protect reproductive freedom in Michigan.

events.title: Knock Doors w/ Congresswoman Debbie Dingell!
events.description: Join Congresswoman Debbie Dingell and the ONE Campaign in Ann Arbor to knock doors & get voters engaged and excited to elect Democrats up and down the ballot! Let's knock on some doors together to remind voters about the importance of this upcoming election and make sure Michigan stays BLUE in 2022.

events.title: Canvass with Jennifer Conlin and Team Debbie Dingell
events.description:
Join Jennifer Conlin, Team Debbie Dingell, volunteers, and staff as we knock on doors in the area! Food, supplies, and beverages will be provided, snacks are encouraged. Working cell phones with service and charged battery are also highly encouraged.

Our goal is to speak with as many neighbors as possible about our campaign and what is at stake, sign up today and forward the event to friends and family!

events.title: Michigan Postcards to Defend the Democratic House Majority
events.description:
Help us make sure Democrats hold the House majority and potentially expand it this November by writing postcard to rally Democrats to vote in 41 competitive House races from California to Maine this November, including three House districts in Michigan: MI-03 (Scholten), MI-07 (Slotkin), MI-08 (Kildee). Our goal is to send 6 million postcards, so we need your help!

You'll need to provide your own postcards and stamps for this program. We recommend https://progressivepostcards.ourproshop.com, an online store that sells postcards with several of our designs for less than most sellers. 

After you sign up, we'll email you a list of voters and instructions, which will include an October mailing date and three message options.

Click the "Take me to the sign up" button to go to the full sign-up page. 

Postcards to Swing States is a project of Progressive Turnout Project. For more information, visit us at turnoutpac.org/postcards or send us an email.

events.title: Carrie Rheingans for MI House! It's Carrie's birthday!
events.description:
Carrie needs your help to produce two final mailers to rural voters. 

Reaching these persuadable voters is must-do to win this critically important new MI House seat to protect our reproductive rights!

Please join us for a casual cocktail hour to celebrate Carrie's 41st birthday, and to get her campaign over the finish line! 

* $50 will fund printing of 500 mailers

* $100 will fund printing of 1,250 mailers

* $250 will fund postage for 625 mailers

And ANY AMOUNT helps!

[Donate here](https://secure.actblue.com/donate/carrie-41-bday)
